# This file contains domains that I want blocked on my network.

#And here's the pattern that Apple recommends using to block regular domains, as it blocks subdomains and is balanced enough, so you are less likely to see any side effects.
#^https?://+([^:/]+\.)?domain\.com[:/]

#Letâ€™s break it down into smaller parts:
#    ^https?://+ matches http:// and https:// and makes sure that there is no text before the URL; 
#    ([^:/]+\.)? targets all subdomains if there are any;
#    domain\.com matches the domain itself;
#    [:/] this tiny part blocks the domain even if the URL contains an extra part after .com. For example, domain.com/page or domain.com:8000

# https://support.1blocker.com/en/articles/6436164-using-regex-to-block-urls

